text: Grayhawk is an unincorporated community and census-designated place in Ste. Genevieve County, Missouri, United States. Its population was 525 as of the 2010 census. ==Geography== According to the U.S. Census Bureau, the community has an area of ; of its area is land, and is water. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Ste.
